& [SLMLexicalSubstrateRebuildWorkflow] is the operational guide for lexical substrate rebuilds
  + [workflow_uuid] is d9fa3b40-2f63-43d7-8ba4-d5b47f29e932
  + [contract] is slm_project/specifications/contracts/SLM_Lexical_Substrate_Delta_Rebuild_Workflow_Contract.sop
  + [default_mode] is dry_run

  & [DryRunCommand] is the safe inspection path
    + [command] is python slm_lexicon/scripts/rebuild_lexical_substrate_workflow.py --dry-run
    = must: print planned commands
    = must: print current artifact checksums
    = must: avoid modifying files

  & [LocalRebuildCommand] is the explicit generated-artifact rebuild path
    + [command] is python slm_lexicon/scripts/rebuild_lexical_substrate_workflow.py --execute-local
    = must: rebuild SQLite/cache/substrate artifacts from already preserved source files
    = must: run source gate after rebuild
    - never: download source data

  & [SourceRefreshCommand] is the explicit source-download path
    + [command] is python slm_lexicon/scripts/rebuild_lexical_substrate_workflow.py --execute-local --include-download
    = must: be used only when intentionally refreshing source authority
    = must: preserve source manifest and checksums
    - never: run as an implicit side effect of ordinary tests

  & [ArtifactBoundary] is the preservation rule
    = must: treat slm_lexicon/data/raw as preserved source material
    = must: treat slm_lexicon/data/slm_lexicon.sqlite and slm_lexicon/data/slm_lexical_substrate as generated artifacts
    = must: review checksum changes before accepting a rebuild
